s:1021:"<p><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;"><strong>Course Completion Requirements: Grammar Essentials</strong></span><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>To complete the Grammar Essentials course, you need to:</p><p><br /></p><p></p><ol><li><strong>Complete All Modules:</strong> Successfully finish each module, covering key topics such as punctuation, sentence structure, and parts of speech.</li><li><strong>Pass Quizzes and Assessments:</strong> Achieve a passing score on all quizzes and assessments to demonstrate your understanding of the material.</li><li><strong>Participate in Discussions:</strong> Engage in Module chats/discussions and activities to apply your knowledge and interact with peers.</li><li><strong>Achieve a Minimum Grade:</strong> Attain the minimum grade set to ensure mastery of the essential grammar concepts.</li></ol><p></p><p><br /></p><p>Upon meeting these requirements, you will have demonstrated a strong grasp of grammar fundamentals, paving the way for improved writing and communication skills.</p>";